The construction works for the luxury Al Zorah Golf Clubhouse which is designed by Architect Anabelle Kassar have begun in Ajman according to Al Zorah Development (Private) Company P.S.C, a partnership between the Government of Ajman and Solidere International, a city maker, place maker, and developer, focused on creating urban destinations and mixed-use real estate developments in the Middle East and emerging markets internationally. Set upon a natural landscape with the scenery of flowing dunes and 1 million meters of mangrove forest, the Al Zorah Golf Clubhouse when completed, will feature an 18-hole championship golf course operated by Troon under the Troon Gold brand and created by Nicklaus Design. The golf club will also be accompanied and complemented by full-on gold and leisure facilities such as a tennis court, swimming pool for children and adults, a purpose-built gymnasium, and a gold shop. Additionally, there will be various food and beverages outlets as well as underground parking available. Also Read: Palace Beach Resort in Fujairah, UAE, to be Launched Soon The leisure clubhouse is projected to boast world-class and international standards that will help put it on the map of premier golfing and tourist destinations, especially in the northern Emirates. The Chief Executive Officer at Al Zorah Development Company, George Saad expressed that the company’s unique world-class golf course is soon to become even more impressive as construction works on projects such as the Al Zorah Golf Clubhouse begin. He further added that the ambition of the Al Zorah Golf Clubhouse is to be able to maintain its position as one of the very best in the Middle Eastern region. He pointed out that the state-of-the-art clubhouse accompanied by an 18-hole championship golf course is all in an effort to strengthen their competitiveness.